
Last update : July 31, 2013
	
in ~/proj/etienne/my_plots/

Plotting procedure of various types.
	
	
	# Relevant non-output functions:

	data_shift.m : Shifts data on a [0:360] longitude grid to
	[-180:180]. This representation highlights land masses better.

	x_cvec.m : Automate contour (or color) vector generation if needed
	and expands it to include out of range values.

	my_cbar.m : Custom colorbar function which implement custom
	alignment, tick marks and tick labels.

----------------------------------------------------------------------
	
	# One plot output:

	plot_hist.m : Computes and plots probability distribution functions
	via performing histograms analysis on a given 1D or 2D array.

	plot_hist2.m : 2nd generation histogram function. Enable several
	line to be plotted at once.

	plot_map_miller.m : Plots the contours of a 2D array on a world map
	using a Miller projection. Coastlines are drawn and the map is
	centered around the Greenwich meridian. 

	plot_map_miller2.m : 2nd generation miller map function. Uses
	my_cbar.m and x_cvec.m.

	plot_locations.m : Plots the coordinate points generated by
	locations.m on a Miller map.
	
	plot_box_regions.m : Plots box regions (box_regions.m) on a Miller
	map.

	plot_ts.m : Plots the time series of a specific vector at one
	location as well as monthly averages and standard deviations for
	comparison

	plot_scatter.m : Generates a scatter of two vectors at one location,
	color-coded to differenciate between months.

	plot_scatter_full.m : Scatter plot all land points of two vectors.
	
	plot_scatter_ccols.m : Color-coded scatter plots w.r.t. a contour
	vector as function of two (state) vectors.

	plot_line.m : Line plot of multiple variable w.r.t. months of the
	year (e.g. JJA, MJJAS, full year) including a measure of the 
	inter-annual spread at each month.

	plot_line_2axes.m : 2-axes verison of plot_line.m (also supports
	2 panels versions)

----------------------------------------------------------------------

	# Multiple panel figures:

	plot_2panels.m : 2x1 miller map panels, 1 color bar.

	plot_3panels.m : 3x1 miller map panels, 1 color bar.

	plot_4panels.m : 2x2 miller map panles, 1 color bar.
	
	plot_5panels.m : 1 + 2x2 miller map panels, 1 color bar.

	plot_6panels.m : 3x2 miller map panels, 1 color bar.

	plot_sc_2panels.m : 2x1 color-coded scatter panels, 1 color bar.
	
	plot_sc_4panels.m : 2x2 color-coded scatter panels, 1 color bar.

	plot_sc_miller.m : 1 color-coded scatter, 1 miller map side-by-side.

	plot_line_2axes.m : see 'One plot output'

	plot_hist2_panels.m : variable-dimension multi-panel histogram plot.

----------------------------------------------------------------------

	# Automating multiple output procedures:

	plot_monthly.m : Calls (new!) plot_map_miller2.m and plot_hist.m for
	each month of (Nmonth x Nlat x Nlon) variable.

	plot_summeravg.m : Calls (new!) plot_map_miller2.m and plot_hist.m
	for the summer-averaged value of a (Nmonth x Nlat x Nlon) variable.

	plot_all.m : Calls plot_monthly.m and plot_summeravg.m in
	succession.

	plot_ts_locs.m : Calls plot_ts.m and plot_hist.m for all locations 
	generated by locations.m

	plot_scatter_locs.m Calls plot_scatter plot_scatter for all
	locations generated by locations.m

	plot_comp_datasets.m : (new!) Loops through all (4) data sets,
	calls plot_4panels.m and plot_hist2.m for a set of variables.
	
	plot_compsc_datasets.m : (new!) same as plot_comp_datasets.m
	but calls plot_sc_4panels.m for color-coded scatter plots.
	
	plot_compobs_datasets.m : (new!) Loops through all (4) data sets
	and U. Del observations,
	calls plot_5panels.m and plot_hist2.m for a set of variables.

---------------------------------------------------------------------

	# Output file type procedure:

	plot_print.m : The 'print' commmand for .png outputs. 

	plot_print_eps.m : The 'print' command for .eps outputs.
	
		Figures : 
		PNG outputs go to ~/proj/etienne/$script_folder/figs/png/
		EPS outputs go to ~/proj/etienne/$script_folder/figs/eps/

---------------------------------------------------------------------

